<sec id="section1-1032373212474439">
<title>Accounting History Special Interest Group</title>
<p><bold>2012 Manuscript Award</bold></p>
<p>is awarded to</p>
<p><bold>Nola Buhr</bold></p>
<p>University of Saskatchewan</p>
<p>for her article entitled</p>
<p><bold>Accrual accounting by Anglo-American governments: Motivations, developments, and some tensions over the last 30 years</bold></p>
<p>which appeared in</p>
<p><bold>Vol.17, No.3-4, August/November 2012</bold></p>
<p>This annual award is judged by the members of the Accounting History Special Interest Group of the Accounting and Finance Association of Australia and New Zealand and is awarded to the author(s) of the article published in the journal which “makes the most significant contribution to the accounting history literature”. The award recipient for 2012 receives a AU$500 prize sponsored by the School of Accountancy, QUT Business School, Queensland University Technology.</p>
